		<h2 class="text-center">North Carolina Driving Privilege</h2>
		<p>Yes, you have read correctly, driving in North Carolina (as in most states) is a privilege and not a right. There are traffic rules and laws that go along with that privilege and violations of such rules or laws can result in a conviction of a moving or non-moving violation - and that conviction - may lead to a suspension of your driving privilege, jail and/or an increase in your car insurance premium.  If you received a ticket that places you in danger of loosing your license or facing jail or an increase in insurance premium, call Attorney Springsteen for a free consultation - at 919.482.8322 - before you get convicted.</p>
	</section>
