			<h3>Moving Violations and The North Carolina Department of Motor Vehicles (NCDMV)</h3>
			<p>According to the NCDMV, a NC Driver, who is convicted of certain moving violations will have points* added to their driving record.
			<br><br>
			The magic number concerning DMV points is 12. If you have 12 points on your license within 3-year period your license will be revoked. If you accumulate 7 points, the DMV has the discretion to require you to attend a driver improvement clinic (fee of $50.00), once completed 3 points are deducted from your record.
			<br><br>
			The length of a driver’s license suspension depends on the reason for which it was suspended. Common causes for suspension are listed below:</p>
